    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Saucers that have wells or frames to hold in place a cup of tea or coffee. The cup and saucer may both be ceramic, or ceramic cups may be paired with silver or other metal saucer components.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047020/Newman, Illustrated Dictionary of Silverware (2000)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para un tipo de marco de metal, generalmente de plata, que sirve de soporte para una taza de cerámica y usualmente de porcelana.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
